The Administrator advising on policy issues fulfils a supranational function within the EPP Group Secretariat and carries out, the following functions and duties:
•	Participating in the political preparation of external meetings of the group;
•	Supporting the strategy team in every of the tasks falling in the competences of the unit;
•	Monitoring the outcome of the meetings, in the field of the expertise, and reporting on these to the hierarchy;
•	Drafting minutes of meetings, speeches, briefing notes, analysis and other documents on the fields of competence
•	Contributing to the definition, shaping and implementation of political strategies of the Group.

